<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" name="viewport"/>
        <link rel="icon" type="img/png" href="./Images/blueStroller.png">
        <title>gaitStroller</title>
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Baskerville&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style2.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="content">
            <a id="signupLink" href="#signup">SIGN UP!</a>
            <h1 id="title">gaitStroller</h1>
            <h2 id="subTitle">a category revolution</h2>
            <img id="logo" src="./Images/blueStroller.png" alt="Logo">

            <img class="mainImg" src="./Images/runnerCompressed.jpg" alt="Gait Stroller Runner">

            <div class="valueProp">
                <div class="valuePropText">
                    <h3>Value Prop One</h3>

                    <p>An ‘extremely credible source’ has called my office and told me that Barack Obama’s placeholder text is a fraud. He’s a word hero because he was captured. I guarantee you there's no problem, I guarantee. I think the only difference between me and the other placeholder text is that I’m more honest and my words are more beautiful. The other thing with Lorem Ipsum is that you have to take out its family.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="spacer"></div>

                <img src="./Images/stroller2.jpg" alt="Runner">
            </div>

            <div class="valueProp">
                <img src="./Images/stroller2.jpg" alt="Runner">

                <div class="spacer"></div>

                <div class="valuePropText">
                    <h3>Value Prop Two</h3>

                    <p>Be careful, or I will spill the beans on your placeholder text. Does everybody know that pig named Lorem Ipsum? I just can't do it. I love Hispanics! It's an art you're basically born with.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="valueProp">
                <div class="valuePropText">
                    <h3>Value Prop Three</h3>

                    <p>Are they small words? If Trump Ipsum weren’t my own words, perhaps I’d be dating it. It's an art you're basically born with. Sadly, it’s no longer a 10. You could see there was text coming out of her eyes, text coming out of her wherever.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="spacer"></div>

                <img src="./Images/stroller2.jpg" alt="Runner">
            </div>

            <form id="signup" action="/phasethree" method="post">
                <label>Name:
                    <input type="text" required>
                </label>
            </form>
        </div>
    </body>

    <script>
        let header = document.getElementById("title");
        let subTitle = document.getElementById("subTitle");
        let distance = document.documentElement.scrollTop;
        let logo = document.getElementById("logo");
        document.getElementById("signupLink").onclick = ()=>{
            header.style.fontSize = `${75 - (250 / 5.5)}px`;
        };

        if(distance < 250){
            header.style.fontSize = `${75 - (distance / 5.5)}px`;
        }else{
            subTitle.style.display = "none";
        }

        window.onscroll = ()=>{
            let distance = document.documentElement.scrollTop;
            if(distance < 250){
                header.style.fontSize = `${75 - (distance / 5.5)}px`;
            }

            if(distance > 325){
                logo.style.position = "fixed";
            }else{
                logo.style.position = "static";
            }
        }
    </script>
</html>